spec: socket_extra2206
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)
error_model: python_exceptions
provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "Python docs — https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html"
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py and Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12"
  not_derived_from:
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave _extra2206: rich comparison operator protocol dict-presence — __lt__, __le__, __gt__, __ge__, __eq__, __ne__."
    - "socket.socket is a Python-level class wrapping a C socket. It defines none of the rich comparison operators in its own __dict__. Sockets are not orderable as objects."
    - "socket.error (alias of OSError) is an exception class. It defines none of the rich comparison operators in its own __dict__."
    - "socket.timeout and socket.gaierror are thin subclasses of OSError. Neither defines rich comparison operators in their own __dict__."
    - "socket.AddressFamily and socket.SocketKind are IntEnum subclasses. Despite inheriting integer comparison behavior via int, neither class defines any rich comparison operator in its own __dict__ — they inherit from IntEnum and int further up the MRO."
    - "socket.socket.__dict__ contains: accept, close, detach, dup, makefile, sendfile, set_inheritable, get_inheritable, type, family, and other socket-specific methods."
    - "socket.AddressFamily.__dict__ contains AF_INET, AF_INET6, AF_UNIX, AF_UNSPEC, AF_LINK, AF_ROUTE, and other address family members."
    - "socket.SocketKind.__dict__ contains SOCK_STREAM, SOCK_DGRAM, SOCK_RAW, SOCK_RDM, SOCK_SEQPACKET and other socket kind members."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-12."
  created_at: "2026-04-12"

